From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: VyOS LS1046A CI <ci@vyos-ls1046a>
Date: Tue, 10 Jun 2026 00:45:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fman/dpaa: wire CC steering end-to-end via the HW-proven
 KGSE_CCBS graft (M3-3b)

fman_cc_tree_install() (board patch 0098) installed the MURAM
match-key/AD/group tables but nothing ever routed frames INTO the tree -
the exact silent non-enforcement failure mode the policer had (BUG 3
steering, fixed 2026-06-09).  This patch closes the M3-3b datapath gap
using the recipe proven on LS1046A silicon (ask20 captures 2026-05-23/25,
PR14z20/PR14z22 + patch 0065: 24M+ frames CC-matched and silicon-forwarded):

  - KGSE_MODE NIA stays at the BMI direct-enqueue default (0x80500002).
    The CC walk is dispatched IMPLICITLY whenever KGSE_CCBS is non-zero.
    Flipping the NIA engine bits to FM_CTL|AC_CC - what the previous
    attach_cc skeleton encoded - was DISPROVEN on hardware (dispatch
    stalled at a few hundred frames; reverted there as patch 0051).
  - KGSE_CCBS carries the MURAM byte offset of the CC root group table.

Changes:

  fman_keygen.c
    - next_engine==2 branch keeps ENQUEUE_KG_DFLT_NIA (no NIA flip) and
      ORs in only the CCOBASE group index; unused NIA_ENG_FM_CTL /
      NIA_FM_CTL_AC_CC defines dropped; comments now document the
      HW-proven semantics (CCBS = group-table offset, implicit CC walk).

  fman_pcd_cc.c / fman_pcd_internal.h
    - new intra-module accessor fman_pcd_cc_tree_group_table_off()
      exposing the tree's root group-table MURAM offset to the KeyGen TU
      (not EXPORT_SYMBOL'd - same idiom as fman_muram_offset_to_vbase).

  fman_pcd_kg.c / fman_pcd.h
    - fman_pcd_kg_attach_cc() made productive: CCBS <- group-table
      offset, save/restore on failure, and ->used cleared before the
      in-place keygen_scheme_setup() reprogram (setup() rejects enable
      on a used scheme, so the old body could never have re-enabled).
    - new exported pair fman_pcd_kg_port_attach_cc() /
      fman_pcd_kg_port_detach_cc(): graft the port's EXISTING lowest-id
      RSS scheme onto an installed tree (mirrors the BUG 3 policer
      steering fix fman_pcd_kg_port_attach_policer()/detach).  RSS
      hashing / match vector / base FQID are preserved so a CC miss
      still spreads over the same hashed RX FQs.

  dpaa_fman_caps.c
    - fman_cc_tree_install() now completes the datapath: after the
      static install it fetches the tree base
      (fman_pcd_cc_static_get_base) and grafts the port scheme
      (fman_pcd_kg_port_attach_cc); on graft failure the tree is torn
      down again (no half-wired state).
    - fman_cc_tree_destroy() detaches the graft FIRST so the silicon
      never walks a freed tree, then releases the MURAM tables.

Native arm64 compile of fman/ + dpaa/: 0 warnings, 0 errors.

M3-3b acceptance (spec sec 5.4): CC tree installs an exact-match key, RX
FQ steers, MURAM allocate->free proven on DUT - the install/steer halves
are now both wired; DUT validation is the remaining step.
---
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_fman_caps.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_fman_caps.c
index 063d3be..e867fa5 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_fman_caps.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_fman_caps.c
@@ -266,6 +266,7 @@ int fman_cc_tree_install(struct fman *fm, u8 port_id,
 {
 struct fman_pcd_cc_hw_spec *hw;
 struct fman_pcd *pcd;
+u32 cc_base;
 u16 i;
 int err;
 
@@ -291,7 +292,24 @@ dpaa_cc_key_to_hw(&spec->keys[i], &hw->keys[i]);
 
 err = fman_pcd_cc_static_install(pcd, port_id, hw);
 kfree(hw);
+if (err)
 return err;
+
+/*
+ * Wire the datapath: graft the port's existing RSS KeyGen scheme
+ * onto the freshly installed tree (KGSE_CCBS <- root group-table
+ * MURAM offset; HW-proven implicit CC dispatch).  Without this
+ * graft the tree is installed but never walked - the exact silent
+ * non-enforcement failure mode the policer had (BUG 3 steering).
+ */
+err = fman_pcd_cc_static_get_base(pcd, port_id, &cc_base);
+if (!err)
+err = fman_pcd_kg_port_attach_cc(pcd, port_id, cc_base);
+if (err) {
+fman_pcd_cc_static_destroy(pcd, port_id);
+return err;
+}
+return 0;
 }
 EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(fman_cc_tree_install);
 
@@ -318,6 +336,11 @@ if (!(dpaa_fman_get_caps() & FMAN_CAP_CC_EXACT_MATCH))
 return;
 pcd = fman_get_pcd(fm);
 if (pcd)
+/*
+ * Detach the KeyGen graft FIRST so the silicon never walks a freed
+ * tree, then release the MURAM tables.
+ */
+(void)fman_pcd_kg_port_detach_cc(pcd, port_id);
 fman_pcd_cc_static_destroy(pcd, port_id);
 }
 EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(fman_cc_tree_destroy);
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_keygen.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_keygen.c
index 3c6cd3e..e4c488e 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_keygen.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_keygen.c
@@ -109,16 +109,20 @@
  */
 #define KG_SCH_MODE_NIA_PLCR		0x40000000
 
-/* KGSE_MODE next-action selector for Coarse Classification (CC): the mode NIA
- * points at the FMan-controller CC action (NIA_ENG_FM_CTL | NIA_FM_CTL_AC_CC)
- * and the CCOBASE field (bits 27:24) carries the CC group-table base index.
- * KGSE_CCBS carries the hash-bit selection. RM 8.7.4 (KGSE_MODE).
- * For the static single-group/single-entry CC tree (board patch 0098) both
- * CCOBASE and CCBS are 0, so KGSE_MODE(CC) = EN | NIA_ENG_FM_CTL |
- * NIA_FM_CTL_AC_CC = 0x80000006 and KGSE_CCBS = 0.
+/* Coarse Classification (CC) chaining - HW-PROVEN recipe (LS1046A FMan v3,
+ * silicon captures 2026-05-23/25): the KGSE_MODE NIA must STAY at the BMI
+ * direct-enqueue default (EN | NIA_ENG_BMI | NIA_BMI_AC_ENQ_FRAME =
+ * 0x80500002).  The CC walk is dispatched IMPLICITLY whenever KGSE_CCBS is
+ * non-zero: CCBS carries the MURAM byte offset of the CC root group table,
+ * and the optional CCOBASE field (KGSE_MODE bits 30:24, SDK fm_kg.c)
+ * selects the group index within it (0 for the single-group static tree of
+ * board patch 0098).  The alternative theory - flipping the NIA engine
+ * bits to FM_CTL|AC_CC (mode 0x80000006/0x80000000) - was DISPROVEN on
+ * hardware: it stalled dispatch at a few hundred frames, while the
+ * CCBS-only graft carried 24M+ frames through CC match -> silicon forward.
+ * The USDPAA SDK concurs: it keeps NIA = BMI|ENQ_FRAME when grafting and
+ * only ORs in CCOBASE.
  */
-#define NIA_ENG_FM_CTL			0x00000000
-#define NIA_FM_CTL_AC_CC		0x00000006
 #define KG_SCH_MODE_CCOBASE_SHIFT	24
 
 /* Hard-coded configuration:
@@ -549,15 +553,15 @@ int keygen_scheme_setup(struct fman_keygen *keygen, u8 scheme_id,
 			tmp_reg |= KG_SCH_MODE_NIA_PLCR | NIA_ENG_PLCR;
 			scheme_regs.kgse_ppc = scheme->policer_profile_id;
 		} else if (scheme->next_engine == 2) {
-			/* Next engine = Coarse Classification: route the
-			 * frame into the installed CC group table. CCOBASE
-			 * (bits 27:24) selects the CC group; CCBS (kgse_ccbs
-			 * below) selects which hash bits index the entry. The
-			 * CC tree-root MURAM base is programmed separately at
-			 * the BMI RX port (FMBM_RCCB) via
-			 * fman_port_set_cc_base().
+			/* Next engine = Coarse Classification.  HW-proven
+			 * recipe (see the CC chaining comment above): keep
+			 * the BMI direct-enqueue NIA - the CC walk fires
+			 * implicitly because KGSE_CCBS (set below) is
+			 * non-zero - and OR in the CCOBASE group index
+			 * (0 for the single-group static tree).  Flipping
+			 * the NIA to FM_CTL|AC_CC stalls dispatch.
 			 */
-			tmp_reg |= NIA_ENG_FM_CTL | NIA_FM_CTL_AC_CC |
+			tmp_reg |= ENQUEUE_KG_DFLT_NIA |
 				(scheme->cc_base_offset <<
 				 KG_SCH_MODE_CCOBASE_SHIFT);
 		} else {
@@ -578,10 +582,10 @@ int keygen_scheme_setup(struct fman_keygen *keygen, u8 scheme_id,
 	 * policer-attach (see BUG 3a above). For the non-policer paths PPC stays 0
 	 * from the memset above.
 	 */
-	/* Coarse Classification Bits Select (KGSE_CCBS): which hash bits index
-	 * the CC group entry. Only meaningful when the mode NIA points at CC;
-	 * left at 0 (from the memset above) otherwise. For the static
-	 * single-entry tree this is 0.
+	/* KGSE_CCBS: MURAM byte offset of the CC root group table.  A
+	 * non-zero CCBS is what dispatches the frame through the CC engine
+	 * on FMan v3 (HW-proven; the NIA stays BMI direct-enqueue).  Zero
+	 * (from the memset above) on every non-CC path.
 	 */
 	if (enable && scheme->next_engine == 2)
 		scheme_regs.kgse_ccbs = scheme->cc_bits_sel;
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_keygen_internal.h b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_keygen_internal.h
index ff96553..a78fedd5 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_keygen_internal.h
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_keygen_internal.h
@@ -89,9 +89,10 @@ struct keygen_scheme {
 				 * valid when next_engine == 2. 0 for the
 				 * static single-group tree.
 				 */
-	u32 cc_bits_sel;	/* CC hash-bit selection (KGSE_CCBS), valid
-				 * when next_engine == 2. 0 for the static
-				 * single-entry tree.
+	u32 cc_bits_sel;	/* MURAM byte offset of the CC root group
+				 * table (KGSE_CCBS).  Non-zero dispatches
+				 * the CC walk (next_engine == 2); the NIA
+				 * stays BMI direct-enqueue (HW-proven).
 				 */
 };
 
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_cc.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_cc.c
index b9492be..cbf79c2 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_cc.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_cc.c
@@ -382,6 +382,17 @@ void fman_pcd_cc_static_destroy(struct fman_pcd *pcd, u8 port_id)
 }
 EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(fman_pcd_cc_static_destroy);
 
+/*
+ * fman_pcd_cc_tree_group_table_off() - MURAM byte offset of a tree's root
+ * group table.  KeyGen grafting writes this offset into KGSE_CCBS; a
+ * non-zero CCBS is what dispatches frames through the CC engine on FMan v3
+ * (HW-proven).  Intra-module helper for fman_pcd_kg.c - not exported.
+ */
+u32 fman_pcd_cc_tree_group_table_off(const struct fman_pcd_cc_tree *t)
+{
+	return t ? (u32)t->group_off : 0;
+}
+
 /*
  * fman_pcd_cc_static_get_base() - fetch the MURAM byte offset of a port's
  * installed static CC tree root (its group table).
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_internal.h b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_internal.h
index ff948fd..66fdb71 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_internal.h
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_internal.h
@@ -42,4 +42,10 @@ struct list_head *fman_pcd_get_manip_list(struct fman_pcd *pcd);
 struct list_head *fman_pcd_get_plcr_list(struct fman_pcd *pcd);
 struct list_head *fman_pcd_get_replic_list(struct fman_pcd *pcd);
 
+/* Intra-module CC-tree accessor (fman_pcd_cc.c -> fman_pcd_kg.c): MURAM
+ * byte offset of the tree's root group table, for the KGSE_CCBS graft.
+ */
+struct fman_pcd_cc_tree;
+u32 fman_pcd_cc_tree_group_table_off(const struct fman_pcd_cc_tree *t);
+
 #endif /* __FMAN_PCD_INTERNAL_H */
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_kg.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_kg.c
index d260f66..aed5d84 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_kg.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_kg.c
@@ -380,6 +380,8 @@ int fman_pcd_kg_attach_cc(struct fman_pcd_kg_scheme *scheme,
 	struct fman *fman;
 	struct fman_keygen *keygen;
 	struct mutex *lock;
+	u32 saved_ccbs;
+	u8 saved_engine;
 	int err;
 
 	if (!scheme || !cc)
@@ -392,15 +394,13 @@ int fman_pcd_kg_attach_cc(struct fman_pcd_kg_scheme *scheme,
 	lock = fman_pcd_get_lock(scheme->pcd);
 
 	/*
-	 * Chain this KeyGen scheme into the installed Coarse Classification
-	 * tree.  The scheme's hash output indexes the CC group table; the
-	 * matched AD result then carries the destination RX FQID.  For the
-	 * static single-group/single-entry tree (board patch 0098) both the
-	 * CCOBASE group index and the CCBS hash-bit selection are 0.
-	 *
-	 * The CC tree-root MURAM base is programmed separately at the BMI RX
-	 * port (FMBM_RCCB) via fman_port_set_cc_base(); this routine only
-	 * flips the KeyGen scheme into CC next-engine mode.
+	 * Graft this KeyGen scheme onto the installed Coarse Classification
+	 * tree using the HW-proven recipe (see fman_keygen.c CC chaining
+	 * comment): KGSE_CCBS <- MURAM offset of the tree's root group
+	 * table; the NIA stays BMI direct-enqueue and the CC walk fires
+	 * implicitly because CCBS is non-zero.  The matched AD result then
+	 * carries the destination RX FQID; a miss falls through to the
+	 * tree's miss action.
 	 *
 	 * Same pattern as the policer (next_engine == 1) path: mutate the
 	 * internal slot then re-run keygen_scheme_setup(enable = true) under
@@ -409,16 +409,26 @@ int fman_pcd_kg_attach_cc(struct fman_pcd_kg_scheme *scheme,
 	 */
 	mutex_lock(lock);
 	slot = &keygen->schemes[scheme->id];
+	saved_engine = slot->next_engine;
+	saved_ccbs   = slot->cc_bits_sel;
+
 	slot->next_engine    = 2;
 	slot->cc_base_offset = 0;
-	slot->cc_bits_sel    = 0;
+	slot->cc_bits_sel    = fman_pcd_cc_tree_group_table_off(cc);
 
+	/*
+	 * keygen_scheme_setup() rejects enable on an already-used scheme
+	 * (-EINVAL), so clear ->used for the in-place reprogram; setup()
+	 * sets it back to true on success.
+	 */
+	slot->used = false;
 	err = keygen_scheme_setup(keygen, (u8)scheme->id, true);
 	if (err) {
-		/* Roll back to the BMI-enqueue default on failure. */
-		slot->next_engine    = 0;
+		/* Roll back to the previous next-engine on failure. */
+		slot->next_engine    = saved_engine;
 		slot->cc_base_offset = 0;
-		slot->cc_bits_sel    = 0;
+		slot->cc_bits_sel    = saved_ccbs;
+		slot->used = false;
 		(void)keygen_scheme_setup(keygen, (u8)scheme->id, true);
 		mutex_unlock(lock);
 		return err;
@@ -586,3 +596,104 @@ int fman_pcd_kg_port_detach_policer(struct fman_pcd *pcd, u8 hw_port_id)
 	return err;
 }
 EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(fman_pcd_kg_port_detach_policer);
+
+int fman_pcd_kg_port_attach_cc(struct fman_pcd *pcd, u8 hw_port_id,
+			       u32 cc_group_off)
+{
+	struct fman_keygen *keygen;
+	struct keygen_scheme *slot;
+	struct fman *fman;
+	struct mutex *lock;
+	u32 saved_ccbs;
+	u8 saved_engine, id;
+	int err;
+
+	if (!pcd || !cc_group_off)
+		return -EINVAL;
+	if (hw_port_id < 0x08 || hw_port_id >= 0x28)
+		return -EINVAL;
+
+	fman = fman_pcd_get_fman(pcd);
+	if (!fman || !fman->keygen)
+		return -ENXIO;
+	keygen = fman->keygen;
+	lock = fman_pcd_get_lock(pcd);
+
+	mutex_lock(lock);
+
+	slot = kg_find_port_scheme(keygen, hw_port_id, &id);
+	if (!slot) {
+		mutex_unlock(lock);
+		return -ENODEV;
+	}
+
+	saved_engine = slot->next_engine;
+	saved_ccbs   = slot->cc_bits_sel;
+
+	/*
+	 * HW-proven CC graft (see fman_keygen.c CC chaining comment):
+	 * KGSE_CCBS <- MURAM offset of the CC root group table; the NIA
+	 * stays BMI direct-enqueue and the CC walk fires implicitly.
+	 * use_hashing / base_fqid / match_vector are untouched, so on a
+	 * CC miss the frame still spreads over the same hashed RX FQs.
+	 */
+	slot->next_engine    = 2;
+	slot->cc_base_offset = 0;
+	slot->cc_bits_sel    = cc_group_off;
+
+	slot->used = false;
+	err = keygen_scheme_setup(keygen, id, true);
+	if (err) {
+		/* Restore the previous next-engine on failure. */
+		slot->next_engine = saved_engine;
+		slot->cc_bits_sel = saved_ccbs;
+		slot->used = false;
+		(void)keygen_scheme_setup(keygen, id, true);
+		mutex_unlock(lock);
+		return err;
+	}
+
+	mutex_unlock(lock);
+	return 0;
+}
+EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(fman_pcd_kg_port_attach_cc);
+
+int fman_pcd_kg_port_detach_cc(struct fman_pcd *pcd, u8 hw_port_id)
+{
+	struct fman_keygen *keygen;
+	struct keygen_scheme *slot;
+	struct fman *fman;
+	struct mutex *lock;
+	u8 id;
+	int err;
+
+	if (!pcd)
+		return -EINVAL;
+	if (hw_port_id < 0x08 || hw_port_id >= 0x28)
+		return -EINVAL;
+
+	fman = fman_pcd_get_fman(pcd);
+	if (!fman || !fman->keygen)
+		return -ENXIO;
+	keygen = fman->keygen;
+	lock = fman_pcd_get_lock(pcd);
+
+	mutex_lock(lock);
+
+	slot = kg_find_port_scheme(keygen, hw_port_id, &id);
+	if (!slot) {
+		/* Nothing bound: detach is a no-op (idempotent teardown). */
+		mutex_unlock(lock);
+		return 0;
+	}
+
+	slot->next_engine    = 0;
+	slot->cc_base_offset = 0;
+	slot->cc_bits_sel    = 0;
+
+	slot->used = false;
+	err = keygen_scheme_setup(keygen, id, true);
+	mutex_unlock(lock);
+	return err;
+}
+EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(fman_pcd_kg_port_detach_cc);
diff --git a/include/linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h b/include/linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h
index 96563a3..41f4b3b 100644
--- a/include/linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h
+++ b/include/linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h
@@ -238,15 +238,46 @@ int fman_pcd_kg_port_detach_policer(struct fman_pcd *pcd, u8 hw_port_id);
  * @scheme: handle from fman_pcd_kg_scheme_create()
  * @cc:     classifier tree from fman_pcd_cc_tree_create()
  *
- * Wires the KGSE_CCBS (CC Base Scheme) register so that the scheme's
- * hash output indexes into the CC tree's key table.
+ * Writes the CC tree's root group-table MURAM offset into KGSE_CCBS;
+ * a non-zero CCBS dispatches frames through the CC engine implicitly
+ * (HW-proven on FMan v3 - the NIA stays BMI direct-enqueue).
  *
- * Return: 0 on success, -EOPNOTSUPP until the CC subsystem lands,
- * -EINVAL on bad args.
+ * Return: 0 on success, -EINVAL on bad args, -ENXIO without KeyGen.
  */
 int fman_pcd_kg_attach_cc(struct fman_pcd_kg_scheme *scheme,
 			  struct fman_pcd_cc_tree *cc);
 
+/**
+ * fman_pcd_kg_port_attach_cc() - graft an RX port's existing RSS scheme
+ * onto an installed CC tree.
+ * @pcd:          PCD subsystem handle (fman_get_pcd())
+ * @hw_port_id:   hardware RX port id (0x08..0x27; eth3 = 0x10)
+ * @cc_group_off: MURAM byte offset of the CC root group table
+ *                (fman_pcd_cc_static_get_base())
+ *
+ * In-place reprogram of the port's lowest-id bound KeyGen scheme: the
+ * RSS hashing, match vector and base FQID are preserved; KGSE_CCBS is
+ * set to @cc_group_off so every frame walks the CC tree first.  A CC
+ * miss falls through to the tree's miss action.
+ *
+ * Return: 0 on success, -ENODEV if the port has no bound scheme,
+ * -EINVAL on bad args, -ENXIO without KeyGen.
+ */
+int fman_pcd_kg_port_attach_cc(struct fman_pcd *pcd, u8 hw_port_id,
+			       u32 cc_group_off);
+
+/**
+ * fman_pcd_kg_port_detach_cc() - restore an RX port's RSS scheme to the
+ * plain BMI-enqueue path (reverse of fman_pcd_kg_port_attach_cc()).
+ * @pcd:        PCD subsystem handle
+ * @hw_port_id: hardware RX port id (0x08..0x27)
+ *
+ * Idempotent: a port with no bound scheme is a no-op.
+ *
+ * Return: 0 on success or if nothing was attached; negative errno.
+ */
+int fman_pcd_kg_port_detach_cc(struct fman_pcd *pcd, u8 hw_port_id);
+
 /**
  * fman_pcd_kg_scheme_destroy() - tear down a previously created scheme.
  * @scheme: handle from fman_pcd_kg_scheme_create().  NULL-safe.
